sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server

    Note right of browser: User types a new note into the text field and clicks the "Save" button

    Note right of browser: Browser executes the event handler in spa.js<br/>It prevents the default form submission<br/>and creates a new note object

    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    Note right of server: Server appends the new note to the data
    server-->>browser: 201 Created (or similar success response)
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: Event handler adds the new note to the local list of notes<br/>and re-renders the notes on the page

    Note right of browser: (Optional) The page may also re-fetch the latest data.json<br/>to ensure consistency, but the primary update is client-side